    "body": "Ok, right. It is on purpose that callcode does not copy storage to memory. The reason is that you can actually pass a storage pointer via callcode, as opposed to call. If you want to force copying to memory, assign the data to a local (memory) variable before calling.\n\nClosing as not a bug.\n",
